    <h1>Generating invoices</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Orders » Fulfillment » Generate invoices</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_generating_invoices">1. Generating invoices</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In this menu, invoices are generated with the help of a <strong>group function</strong>. For example, all invoices that have currently been cleared for shipping could be generated with a search request that has <strong>order status [5] cleared for shipping</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_options">2. Options</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can carry out settings related to the <strong>layout</strong> of the invoices by going to <strong>Settings » Client (store) » Select store » Locations » Select location » Documents</strong>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>Settings &gt; Orders &gt; Event procedures</strong> in order to define which additional <strong>procedure(s)</strong> should be carried out when the invoice is generated. For example, you can configure an <strong>event procedure</strong> for automatically sending the invoice with an E-mail template.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Tip</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This menu also contains a direct link to the <strong>Event procedures</strong> menu. It can be accessed by clicking on the <strong>Event procedure</strong> link.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_generating_invoices_2">3. Generating invoices</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Generating invoices:</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>generate invoices</strong> (see path above).</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Pay attention to the explanations given in table 1 and carry out the <strong>settings</strong> for the <strong>search filter</strong> as desired.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Under <strong>procedure</strong>, select an <strong>invoice date</strong> and the <strong>order status</strong> that you would like to have assigned to the selected orders after the invoices were successfully created.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Click on the <strong>gear-wheel icon</strong> after having selected all of the options.<br>
→ You will receive a <strong>PDF file</strong>, which contains the invoices of all the orders that match the filter options you selected.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
